    {
      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "I need to make all text-dense sections collapsible in the file `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\logo_deconstruction.html`. The CSS has already been added with classes `collapse`, `glossary-item`, `adr-item`, and `.collapse-body`. \n\nNOW do these transformations:\n\n## 1. GLOSSARY ENTRIES (Section 07, ~48 entries)\n\nEach glossary entry is currently a `<div>` with inline style `background:var(--surface2); border-radius:8px; padding:16px; margin-bottom:16px; border-left:3px solid var(--accent);`\n\nEach MUST become:\n```html\n<details class=\"collapse glossary-item\">\n    <summary>TERM NAME</summary>\n    <div class=\"collapse-body\">\n        ... all the <p> content ...\n    </div>\n</details>\n```\n\nThe term name is inside `<div style=\"font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;\">TERM NAME</div>` — extract the TERM NAME text.\n\nThe content after the term name div (the <p> elements, etc.) goes inside `<div class=\"collapse-body\">`.\n\nThe closing `</div>` of each entry becomes `</div></details>`.\n\nDo this for EVERY glossary entry across all letter sections (A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, K, L, M, N, O, P, R, S, T, U, V, W).\n\n## 2. ADR ENTRIES (Section 08, 15 entries)\n\nEach ADR entry is currently a `<div>` with inline style `background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:12px; padding:24px; margin-bottom:20px;`\n\nEach MUST become:\n```html\n<details class=\"collapse adr-item\">\n    <summary>\n        <span>ADR-XXX — Title</span>\n        <span class=\"status-badge\">Status: <span class=\"accepted\">Accepted</span></span>\n    </summary>\n    <div class=\"collapse-body\">\n        ... all the Context, Decision, Alternatives, Consequences, etc. ...\n    </div>\n</details>\n```\n\nThe summary should contain the ADR title line (the `div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:space-between...\"` content, but simplified to just the text and status badge).\n\nMove the status badge div content into `<span class=\"status-badge\">`.\n\nThe closing `</div>` of each ADR entry becomes `</div></details>`.\n\n## 3. LETTER HEADING SECTIONS\n\nMake each letter group heading (e.g., `<div id=\"gloss-A\" style=\"margin-bottom:32px;\">`) collapsible too. Wrap the entire letter section in a `<details class=\"collapse\">` with a `<summary>` containing the letter heading text (like `<h3>A</h3>`).\n\nREAD the file first to understand the exact patterns, then perform all replacements. Verify the file is valid HTML after all changes.\n\nReturn: \"Done — all glossary and ADR entries made collapsible\" with a count of items modified.",
      "timestamp": 1781576288296
