      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\logo_deconstruction.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: <!DOCTYPE html>\n2: <html lang=\"en\">\n3: <head>\n4: <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n5: <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n6: <title>AFJ Cardiff Logo — Deconstruction & Design Tokens</title>\n7: <style>\n8: @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap');\n9: :root {\n10:     --bg: #0a0a0c;\n11:     --surface: #121216;\n12:     --surface2: #1a1a22;\n13:     --border: #2a2a35;\n14:     --text: #f0f0f2;\n15:     --text-dim: #888899;\n16:     --accent: #c08040;\n17:     --accent2: #c04060;\n18:     --red: #ef4444;\n19:     --green: #22c55e;\n20:     --font: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;\n21:     --mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n22: }\n23: * { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }\n24: \n25: /* Collapsible Elements */\n26: details.collapse {\n27:     background: var(--surface);\n28:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n29:     border-radius: 10px;\n30:     overflow: hidden;\n31:     transition: border-color 0.2s;\n32: }\n33: details.collapse[open] {\n34:     border-color: var(--accent);\n35: }\n36: details.collapse > summary {\n37:     cursor: pointer;\n38:     padding: 16px 20px;\n39:     list-style: none;\n40:     display: flex;\n41:     justify-content: space-between;\n42:     align-items: center;\n43:     gap: 12px;\n44:     user-select: none;\n45:     font-weight: 500;\n46: }\n47: details.collapse > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }\n48: details.collapse > summary::after {\n49:     content: '\\25BC';\n50:     font-size: 0.7rem;\n51:     color: var(--accent);\n52:     transition: transform 0.25s ease;\n53:     flex-shrink: 0;\n54: }\n55: details.collapse[open] > summary::after {\n56:     transform: rotate(180deg);\n57: }\n58: details.collapse > summary:hover {\n59:     background: rgba(192,128,64,0.05);\n60: }\n61: details.collapse > .collapse-body {\n62:     padding: 0 20px 20px;\n63: }\n64: details.collapse.glossary-item {\n65:     background: var(--surface2);\n66:     border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);\n67:     margin-bottom: 14px;\n68: }\n69: details.collapse.glossary-item > summary {\n70:     padding: 14px 18px;\n71:     font-family: var(--mono);\n72:     font-size: 0.9rem;\n73:     color: var(--accent);\n74:     font-weight: 600;\n75: }\n76: details.collapse.glossary-item > summary:hover {\n77:     background: rgba(192,128,64,0.08);\n78: }\n79: details.collapse.adr-item { margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0; }\n80: details.collapse.adr-item > summary {\n81:     padding: 20px 24px;\n82:     font-family: var(--mono);\n83:     font-size: 1.05rem;\n84:     color: var(--accent);\n85:     font-weight: 600;\n86:     border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;\n87: }\n88: details.collapse.adr-item[open] > summary {\n89:     border-bottom-color: var(--border);\n90: }\n91: details.collapse.adr-item > .collapse-body {\n92:     padding: 4px 24px 20px;\n93: }\n94: details.collapse.adr-item .status-badge {\n95:     font-family: var(--mono);\n96:     font-size: 0.7rem;\n97:     color: var(--text-dim);\n98:     background: var(--surface2);\n99:     padding: 3px 10px;\n100:     border-radius: 20px;\n101:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n102:     white-space: nowrap;\n103: }\n104: details.collapse.adr-item .status-badge .accepted { color: var(--green); }\n105: \n106: /* Force all collapse bodies to obey padding */\n107: .collapse-body > *:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }\n108: .collapse-body > *:first-child { margin-top: 0; }\n109: \n110: body {\n111:     background: var(--bg);\n112:     color: var(--text);\n113:     font-family: var(--font);\n114:     line-height: 1.6;\n115:     padding: 40px 20px;\n116: }\n117: .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }\n118: \n119: /* Header */\n120: .header {\n121:     text-align: center;\n122:     padding: 60px 0 40px;\n123:     border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n124:     margin-bottom: 50px;\n125: }\n126: .header h1 {\n127:     font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);\n128:     font-weight: 700;\n129:     letter-spacing: -1px;\n130:     background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 30%, var(--accent) 70%, var(--accent2) 100%);\n131:     -webkit-background-clip: text;\n132:     -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;\n133: }\n134: .header p {\n135:     color: var(--text-dim);\n136:     font-size: 1.1rem;\n137:     margin-top: 12px;\n138: }\n139: \n140: /* Section */\n141: .section {\n142:     margin-bottom: 60px;\n143: }\n144: .section-title {\n145:     font-size: 1.5rem;\n146:     font-weight: 600;\n147:     margin-bottom: 24px;\n148:     padding-bottom: 8px;\n149:     border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);\n150:     display: inline-block;\n151: }\n152: \n153: /* Grid Layout */\n154: .grid-2 {\n155:     display: grid;\n156:     grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n157:     gap: 24px;\n158: }\n159: @media (max-width: 768px) {\n160:     .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }\n161: }\n162: .grid-3 {\n163:     display: grid;\n164:     grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);\n165:     gap: 20px;\n166: }\n167: @media (max-width: 900px) {\n168:     .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }\n169: }\n170: @media (max-width: 600px) {\n171:     .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }\n172: }\n173: \n174: /* Card */\n175: .card {\n176:     background: var(--surface);\n177:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n178:     border-radius: 12px;\n179:     padding: 24px;\n180: }\n181: .card h3 {\n182:     font-size: 1rem;\n183:     font-weight: 600;\n184:     margin-bottom: 16px;\n185:     color: var(--accent);\n186:     text-transform: uppercase;\n187:     letter-spacing: 1px;\n188: }\n189: \n190: /* Token Table */\n191: .token-table {\n192:     width: 100%;\n193:     border-collapse: collapse;\n194:     font-family: var(--mono);\n195:     font-size: 0.85rem;\n196: }\n197: .token-table th, .token-table td {\n198:     padding: 8px 12px;\n199:     text-align: left;\n200:     border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n201: }\n202: .token-table th {\n203:     color: var(--text-dim);\n204:     font-weight: 500;\n205:     text-transform: uppercase;\n206:     font-size: 0.75rem;\n207:     letter-spacing: 1px;\n208: }\n209: .token-table td:first-child {\n210:     color: var(--accent);\n211:     font-weight: 500;\n212: }\n213: .token-table td:last-child {\n214:     text-align: right;\n215:     font-weight: 500;\n216: }\n217: \n218: /* Color Swatch */\n219: .swatch-grid {\n220:     display: flex;\n221:     flex-wrap: wrap;\n222:     gap: 8px;\n223: }\n224: .swatch {\n225:     width: 48px;\n226:     height: 48px;\n227:     border-radius: 8px;\n228:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n229:     position: relative;\n230:     cursor: pointer;\n231: }\n232: .swatch:hover::after {\n233:     content: attr(data-color);\n234:     position: absolute;\n235:     bottom: -24px;\n236:     left: 50%;\n237:     transform: translateX(-50%);\n238:     background: var(--surface2);\n239:     padding: 2px 8px;\n240:     border-radius: 4px;\n241:     font-size: 0.7rem;\n242:     font-family: var(--mono);\n243:     white-space: nowrap;\n244:     z-index: 10;\n245: }\n246: \n247: /* Logo Canvas Area */\n248: .logo-viewer {\n249:     position: relative;\n250:     background: var(--surface);\n251:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n252:     border-radius: 12px;\n253:     padding: 20px;\n254:     text-align: center;\n255: }\n256: .logo-viewer img {\n257:     max-width: 100%;\n258:     height: auto;\n259:     max-height: 500px;\n260: }\n261: .logo-controls {\n262:     display: flex;\n263:     gap: 8px;\n264:     margin-top: 16px;\n265:     justify-content: center;\n266:     flex-wrap: wrap;\n267: }\n268: .logo-controls button {\n269:     padding: 6px 16px;\n270:     border-radius: 6px;\n271:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n272:     background: var(--surface2);\n273:     color: var(--text);\n274:     font-family: var(--mono);\n275:     font-size: 0.75rem;\n276:     cursor: pointer;\n277:     transition: all 0.2s;\n278: }\n279: .logo-controls button:hover, .logo-controls button.active {\n280:     border-color: var(--accent);\n281:     background: rgba(192, 128, 96, 0.15);\n282: }\n283: \n284: /* Step Timeline */\n285: .step {\n286:     display: flex;\n287:     gap: 20px;\n288:     padding: 20px 0;\n289:     position: relative;\n290: }\n291: .step:not(:last-child)::before {\n292:     content: '';\n293:     position: absolute;\n294:     left: 20px;\n295:     top: 60px;\n296:     bottom: 0;\n297:     width: 2px;\n298:     background: var(--border);\n299: }\n300: .step-num {\n301:     width: 42px;\n302:     height: 42px;\n303:     border-radius: 50%;\n304:     background: var(--accent);\n305:     color: #fff;\n306:     display: flex;\n307:     align-items: center;\n308:     justify-content: center;\n309:     font-weight: 700;\n310:     font-size: 1rem;\n311:     flex-shrink: 0;\n312: }\n313: .step-content {\n314:     flex: 1;\n315: }\n316: .step-content h3 {\n317:     font-size: 1.2rem;\n318:     font-weight: 600;\n319:     margin-bottom: 8px;\n320: }\n321: .step-content p {\n322:     color: var(--text-dim);\n323:     font-size: 0.95rem;\n324:     margin-bottom: 12px;\n325: }\n326: .step-content .code {\n327:     background: var(--surface2);\n328:     padding: 12px;\n329:     border-radius: 8px;\n330:     font-family: var(--mono);\n331:     font-size: 0.8rem;\n332:     overflow-x: auto;\n333:     color: var(--accent);\n334:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n335: }\n336: \n337: /* Stat Badge */\n338: .stat {\n339:     display: inline-flex;\n340:     align-items: center;\n341:     gap: 6px;\n342:     background: var(--surface2);\n343:     padding: 4px 12px;\n344:     border-radius: 20px;\n345:     font-family: var(--mono);\n346:     font-size: 0.8rem;\n347:     border: 1px solid var(--border);\n348: }\n349: .stat .val { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }\n350: \n351: /* Token row in design tokens section */\n352: .token-row {\n353:     display: flex;\n354:     justify-content: space-between;\n355:     padding: 10px 0;\n356:     border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n357:     font-family: var(--mono);\n358:     font-size: 0.85rem;\n359: }\n360: .token-row .token { color: var(--accent); }\n361: .token-row .value { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }\n362: .token-row .desc { color: var(--text-dim); font-size: 0.75rem; }\n363: \n364: /* Canvas */\n365: #analysisCanvas {\n366:     width: 100%;\n367:     height: auto;\n368:     border-radius: 8px;\n369:     background: #fff;\n370: }\n371: </style>\n372: </head>\n373: <body>\n374: <div class=\"container\">\n375: \n376: <div class=\"header\">\n377:     <h1>AFJ Cardiff / Logo Deconstruction</h1>\n378:     <p>Full design token extraction & step-by-step construction breakdown</p>\n379:     <div style=\"margin-top: 16px; display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;\">\n380:         <span class=\"stat\">Dimensions <span class=\"val\">974 &times; 992</span></span>\n381:         <span class=\"stat\">Aspect Ratio <span class=\"val\">487:496</span></span>\n382:         <span class=\"stat\">DPI <span class=\"val\">216</span></span>\n383:         <span class=\"stat\">Symmetry <span class=\"val\">94.5%</span></span>\n384:     </div>\n385: </div>\n386: \n387: <!-- 1. Logo Viewer with Overlay Controls -->\n388: <div class=\"section\">\n389:     <h2 class=\"section-title\">01 &middot; Raw Canvas</h2>\n390:     <div class=\"logo-viewer\">\n391:         <div style=\"position:relative; display:inline-block;\">\n392:             <canvas id=\"analysisCanvas\" width=\"974\" height=\"992\"></canvas>\n393:         </div>\n394:         <div class=\"logo-controls\">\n395:             <button class=\"active\" data-mode=\"original\">Original</button>\n396:             <button data-mode=\"grid\">Grid</button>\n397:             <button data-mode=\"bbox\">Bounding Box</button>\n398:             <button data-mode=\"edges\">Edge Detect</button>\n399:             <button data-mode=\"centers\">Centers</button>\n400:             <button data-mode=\"all\">All Overlays</button>\n401:         </div>\n402:     </div>\n403: </div>\n404: \n405: <!-- 2. Design Tokens -->\n406: <div class=\"section\">\n407:     <h2 class=\"section-title\">02 &middot; Design Tokens</h2>\n408:     <div class=\"grid-2\">\n409:         <div class=\"card\">\n410:             <h3>Dimensions</h3>\n411:             <div class=\"token-table\">\n412:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">canvas.width</span><span class=\"value\">974px</span><span class=\"desc\">absolute</span></div>\n413:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">canvas.height</span><span class=\"value\">992px</span><span class=\"desc\">absolute</span></div>\n414:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">aspect.ratio</span><span class=\"value\">0.9819</span><span class=\"desc\">487:496</span></div>\n415:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">dpi</span><span class=\"value\">216</span><span class=\"desc\">print quality</span></div>\n416:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">channels</span><span class=\"value\">RGB</span><span class=\"desc\">no alpha</span></div>\n417:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">file.size</span><span class=\"value\">65,024 B</span><span class=\"desc\">PNG</span></div>\n418:             </div>\n419:         </div>\n420:         <div class=\"card\">\n421:             <h3>Content Geometry</h3>\n422:             <div class=\"token-table\">\n423:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">content.x</span><span class=\"value\">209px</span><span class=\"desc\">21.5% from left</span></div>\n424:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">content.y</span><span class=\"value\">238px</span><span class=\"desc\">24.0% from top</span></div>\n425:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">content.width</span><span class=\"value\">468px</span><span class=\"desc\">48.0% of canvas</span></div>\n426:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">content.height</span><span class=\"value\">462px</span><span class=\"desc\">46.6% of canvas</span></div>\n427:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">margin.left</span><span class=\"value\">209px (21.5%)</span><span class=\"desc\">left padding</span></div>\n428:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">margin.right</span><span class=\"value\">297px (30.5%)</span><span class=\"desc\">right padding</span></div>\n429:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">margin.top</span><span class=\"value\">238px (24.0%)</span><span class=\"desc\">top padding</span></div>\n430:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">margin.bottom</span><span class=\"value\">292px (29.4%)</span><span class=\"desc\">bottom padding</span></div>\n431:             </div>\n432:         </div>\n433:     </div>\n434: \n435:     <div class=\"grid-2\" style=\"margin-top:24px;\">\n436:         <div class=\"card\">\n437:             <h3>Color Palette</h3>\n438:             <div class=\"swatch-grid\" id=\"paletteGrid\"></div>\n439:             <div style=\"margin-top:16px;\">\n440:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">primary.bg</span><span class=\"value\">#000000</span><span class=\"desc\">92.1% coverage</span></div>\n441:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">accent.1</span><span class=\"value\">#c08060</span><span class=\"desc\">19.0% - copper/bronze</span></div>\n442:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">accent.2</span><span class=\"value\">#c08040</span><span class=\"desc\">12.6% - gold/brass</span></div>\n443:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">accent.3</span><span class=\"value\">#c0a040</span><span class=\"desc\">12.4% - amber/gold</span></div>\n444:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">accent.4</span><span class=\"value\">#c04060</span><span class=\"desc\">12.3% - crimson/rose</span></div>\n445:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">accent.5</span><span class=\"value\">#c06060</span><span class=\"desc\">11.7% - brick red</span></div>\n446:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">color.count</span><span class=\"value\">7,961</span><span class=\"desc\">unique (incl. anti-alias)</span></div>\n447:             </div>\n448:         </div>\n449:         <div class=\"card\">\n450:             <h3>Structure</h3>\n451:             <div class=\"token-table\">\n452:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">contours</span><span class=\"value\">38</span><span class=\"desc\">external edge paths</span></div>\n453:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">major.regions</span><span class=\"value\">1</span><span class=\"desc\">&gt;1000px area</span></div>\n454:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">components</span><span class=\"value\">29</span><span class=\"desc\">connected regions</span></div>\n455:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">symmetry.h</span><span class=\"value\">94.5%</span><span class=\"desc\">left-right mirror</span></div>\n456:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">symmetry.v</span><span class=\"value\">93.4%</span><span class=\"desc\">top-bottom mirror</span></div>\n457:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">edge.density</span><span class=\"value\">0.91%</span><span class=\"desc\">proportion of edges</span></div>\n458:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">typography.lines</span><span class=\"value\">~14</span><span class=\"desc\">estimated text rows</span></div>\n459:             </div>\n460:         </div>\n461:     </div>\n462: </div>\n463: \n464: <!-- 3. Color Architecture -->\n465: <div class=\"section\">\n466:     <h2 class=\"section-title\">03 &middot; Color Architecture</h2>\n467:     <div class=\"card\">\n468:         <p style=\"color:var(--text-dim); margin-bottom:24px;\">\n469:         The logo is 92.1% pure black (#000000) background with a <strong>warm earth-and-fire accent palette</strong>\n470:         of copper, gold, amber, crimson, and brick red. These warm tones occupy ~7.6% of the canvas and\n471:         are applied to the African continent outline and typography via a gradient that shifts from\n472:         copper/bronze through gold to crimson — evoking the fire, earth, and energy of African dance.\n473:         </p>\n474:         <div class=\"grid-3\">\n475:             <div>\n476:                 <h3 style=\"color:var(--accent); font-size:0.9rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1px; margin-bottom:12px;\">Black Base</h3>\n477:                 <div style=\"background:#000; border-radius:8px; height:80px; border:1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom:8px;\"></div>\n478:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#000000</span><span class=\"value\">92.1%</span></div>\n479:             </div>\n480:             <div>\n481:                 <h3 style=\"color:var(--accent); font-size:0.9rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1px; margin-bottom:12px;\">Warm Gradient</h3>\n482:                 <div style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg, #c08060, #c04060); border-radius:8px; height:80px; border:1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom:8px;\"></div>\n483:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#c08060 &rarr; #c04060</span><span class=\"value\">7.6%</span></div>\n484:             </div>\n485:             <div>\n486:                 <h3 style=\"color:var(--accent); font-size:0.9rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1px; margin-bottom:12px;\">Light Accent</h3>\n487:                 <div style=\"background:linear-gradient(135deg, #c0a040, #e0e0e0); border-radius:8px; height:80px; border:1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom:8px;\"></div>\n488:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#c0a040 &rarr; #ffffff</span><span class=\"value\">~2%</span></div>\n489:             </div>\n490:         </div>\n491:         <div style=\"margin-top:32px; padding-top:24px; border-top:1px solid var(--border);\">\n492:             <h3 style=\"font-size:1rem; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:16px;\">Color Family Breakdown</h3>\n493:             <div class=\"grid-2\" style=\"grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;\">\n494:                 <div>\n495:                     <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">Copper/Bronze</span><span class=\"value\">#c08060</span><span class=\"desc\">19.0% of accent</span></div>\n496:                     <div style=\"background:#c08060; border-radius:6px; height:24px; margin:4px 0 16px; border:1px solid var(--border);\"></div>\n497:                 </div>\n498:                 <div>\n499:                     <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">Gold/Brass</span><span class=\"value\">#c08040</span><span class=\"desc\">12.6% of accent</span></div>\n500:                     <div style=\"background:#c08040; border-radius:6px; height:24px; margin:4px 0 16px; border:1px solid var(--border);\"></div>\n501:                 </div>\n502:                 <div>\n503:                     <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">Amber/Gold</span><span class=\"value\">#c0a040</span><span class=\"desc\">12.4% of accent</span></div>\n504:                     <div style=\"background:#c0a040; border-radius:6px; height:24px; margin:4px 0 16px; border:1px solid var(--border);\"></div>\n505:                 </div>\n506:                 <div>\n507:                     <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">Crimson/Rose</span><span class=\"value\">#c04060</span><span class=\"desc\">12.3% of accent</span></div>\n508:                     <div style=\"background:#c04060; border-radius:6px; height:24px; margin:4px 0 16px; border:1px solid var(--border);\"></div>\n509:                 </div>\n510:                 <div>\n511:                     <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">Brick Red</span><span class=\"value\">#c06060</span><span class=\"desc\">11.7% of accent</span></div>\n512:                     <div style=\"background:#c06060; border-radius:6px; height:24px; margin:4px 0 16px; border:1px solid var(--border);\"></div>\n513:                 </div>\n514:                 <div>\n515:                     <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">Pale Gold</span><span class=\"value\">#c0a060</span><span class=\"desc\">1.5% of accent</span></div>\n516:                     <div style=\"background:#c0a060; border-radius:6px; height:24px; margin:4px 0 16px; border:1px solid var(--border);\"></div>\n517:                 </div>\n518:             </div>\n519:         </div>\n520:     </div>\n521: </div>\n522: \n523: <!-- 4. Step-by-Step Construction -->\n524: <div class=\"section\">\n525:     <h2 class=\"section-title\">04 &middot; Construction Walkthrough</h2>\n526: \n527:     <div class=\"step\">\n528:         <div class=\"step-num\">1</div>\n529:         <div class=\"step-content\">\n530:             <h3>Canvas Setup</h3>\n531:             <p>974 &times; 992px canvas at 216 DPI. Aspect ratio 487:496 (nearly 1:1 square).</p>\n532:             <p>This near-square format allows the African continent outline and \"AFJ CARDIFF\" \n533:             typography to stack vertically while maintaining balanced margins on all sides.</p>\n534:             <div class=\"code\">canvas: { width: 974px, height: 992px, aspectRatio: 0.982, dpi: 216 }</div>\n535:         </div>\n536:     </div>\n537: \n538:     <div class=\"step\">\n539:         <div class=\"step-num\">2</div>\n540:         <div class=\"step-content\">\n541:             <h3>African Continent (Primary Element)</h3>\n542:             <p>The central visual element is the African continent silhouette, placed at \n543:             x=209, y=238 with dimensions 468&times;462px. It occupies 22.7% of the canvas area \n544:             and is centered near-horizontally (content center at x=443 vs canvas center x=487, \n545:             only 44px offset).</p>\n546:             <p>The continent is rendered with a warm copper-to-crimson gradient (#c08060 &rarr; #c04060) \n547:             on a pure black background, creating a distinctive fire-and-earth glow that evokes \n548:             the energy of African dance and the warmth of the continent's cultural heritage.</p>\n549:             <div class=\"code\">africa: { x: 209, y: 238, w: 468, h: 462, gradient: &quot;#c08060-#c04060&quot; }</div>\n550:         </div>\n551:     </div>\n552: \n553:     <div class=\"step\">\n554:         <div class=\"step-num\">3</div>\n555:         <div class=\"step-content\">\n556:             <h3>Typography &mdash; \"AFJ\" Acronym</h3>\n557:             <p>At the top of the composition, the acronym \"AFJ\" is set in a bold sans-serif \n558:             typeface. 14 text rows are estimated from horizontal projection analysis. The \n559:             letters use the same copper-to-crimson gradient as the continent, creating visual \n560:             unity across the brand mark.</p>\n561:             <p>The typography is tightly kerned and sits above the continent with minimal \n562:             leading, creating a cohesive lockup where text and icon are read as one unit.</p>\n563:         </div>\n564:     </div>\n565: \n566:     <div class=\"step\">\n567:         <div class=\"step-num\">4</div>\n568:         <div class=\"step-content\">\n569:             <h3>Typography &mdash; \"CARDIFF\" Wordmark</h3>\n570:             <p>Below the continent, \"CARDIFF\" is set in all-caps. The text region spans from \n571:             approximately y=742 to y=764 (22px height per row). Individual character \n572:             components are detected as connected regions 2 through 11 in the segmentation \n573:             analysis, each with areas between 86&ndash;240px<sup>2</sup>.</p>\n574:             <p>The wordmark is considerably smaller than \"AFJ\", establishing a clear visual \n575:             hierarchy: brand name dominates, location is secondary.</p>\n576:         </div>\n577:     </div>\n578: \n579:     <div class=\"step\">\n580:         <div class=\"step-num\">5</div>\n581:         <div class=\"step-content\">\n582:             <h3>White Space &amp; Margins</h3>\n583:             <p>The content block is surrounded by generous margins: 21.5% left, 30.5% right, \n584:             24% top, 29.4% bottom. This asymmetric margin distribution creates a subtle \n585:             upward-left weighting that draws the eye toward the continent before descending \n586:             to the wordmark.</p>\n587:             <p>The bottom margin is largest (29.4%) — intentional negative space that prevents \n588:             the logo from feeling bottom-heavy despite the stacked vertical layout.</p>\n589:             <div class=\"code\">margins: { left: 21.5%, right: 30.5%, top: 24.0%, bottom: 29.4% }</div>\n590:         </div>\n591:     </div>\n592: \n593:     <div class=\"step\">\n594:         <div class=\"step-num\">6</div>\n595:         <div class=\"step-content\">\n596:             <h3>Symmetry &amp; Balance</h3>\n597:             <p>94.5% horizontal symmetry confirms near-perfect left-right mirroring — the \n598:             continent outline and centered typography are precisely balanced. The 5.5% \n599:             asymmetry is due to the natural irregularity of the African coastline and \n600:             anti-aliasing at edges.</p>\n601:             <p>93.4% vertical symmetry indicates the top-heavy nature is intentional: the \n602:             continent creates visual weight above center, counterbalanced by the smaller \n603:             wordmark below.</p>\n604:         </div>\n605:     </div>\n606: </div>\n607: \n608: <!-- 5. Dual Brand System -->\n609: <div class=\"section\">\n610:     <h2 class=\"section-title\">05 &middot; Dual Color System</h2>\n611:     <div class=\"card\">\n612:         <p style=\"color:var(--text-dim); margin-bottom:24px;\">\n613:         AFJ Cardiff operates a <strong>dual color system</strong>: the brand identity uses warm earth-and-fire \n614:         tones (copper, gold, amber, crimson), while the classroom/UI environment uses cool \n615:         navy-and-charcoal tones. This creates visual contrast — the warm logo pops against \n616:         the cool dark UI backgrounds.\n617:         </p>\n618:         <div class=\"grid-3\">\n619:             <div>\n620:                 <h3 style=\"font-size:0.9rem; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:12px; color:#c08040;\">Logo Palette</h3>\n621:                 <div style=\"display:flex; gap:4px; margin-bottom:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;\">\n622:                     <div style=\"background:#c08060; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#c08060 Copper\"></div>\n623:                     <div style=\"background:#c08040; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#c08040 Gold\"></div>\n624:                     <div style=\"background:#c0a040; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#c0a040 Amber\"></div>\n625:                     <div style=\"background:#c04060; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#c04060 Crimson\"></div>\n626:                     <div style=\"background:#c06060; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#c06060 Brick\"></div>\n627:                 </div>\n628:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#c08060</span><span class=\"value\">19.0%</span><span class=\"desc\">copper</span></div>\n629:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#c08040</span><span class=\"value\">12.6%</span><span class=\"desc\">gold</span></div>\n630:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#c0a040</span><span class=\"value\">12.4%</span><span class=\"desc\">amber</span></div>\n631:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#c04060</span><span class=\"value\">12.3%</span><span class=\"desc\">crimson</span></div>\n632:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#c06060</span><span class=\"value\">11.7%</span><span class=\"desc\">brick</span></div>\n633:             </div>\n634:             <div>\n635:                 <h3 style=\"font-size:0.9rem; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:12px; color:#204060;\">Classroom UI Palette</h3>\n636:                 <div style=\"display:flex; gap:4px; margin-bottom:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;\">\n637:                     <div style=\"background:#202040; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#202040 Dark navy\"></div>\n638:                     <div style=\"background:#204060; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#204060 Navy\"></div>\n639:                     <div style=\"background:#204080; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#204080 Blue\"></div>\n640:                     <div style=\"background:#4060a0; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#4060a0 Medium blue\"></div>\n641:                     <div style=\"background:#202020; width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border);\" title=\"#202020 Charcoal\"></div>\n642:                 </div>\n643:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#202040</span><span class=\"value\">12.7%</span><span class=\"desc\">dark navy</span></div>\n644:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#204060</span><span class=\"value\">11.3%</span><span class=\"desc\">navy</span></div>\n645:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#204080</span><span class=\"value\">9.5%</span><span class=\"desc\">blue</span></div>\n646:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#4060a0</span><span class=\"value\">5.4%</span><span class=\"desc\">medium blue</span></div>\n647:                 <div class=\"token-row\"><span class=\"token\">#202020</span><span class=\"value\">10.1%</span><span class=\"desc\">charcoal</span></div>\n648:             </div>\n649:             <div>\n650:                 <h3 style=\"font-size:0.9rem; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:12px; color:#888;\">How They Work Together</h3>\n651:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7;\">\n652:                 <strong>Logo (warm)</strong> on <strong>Classroom (cool)</strong> creates \n653:                 maximum contrast via complementary color theory. The copper and gold of the \n654:                 logo are warm tones (hue ~30&deg;), while the navy backgrounds are cool \n655:                 (hue ~220&deg;). This 190&deg; separation means the logo pops dramatically \n656:                 against the UI.<br><br>\n657:                 The crimson accent (#c04060) adds energy and passion — appropriate for a \n658:                 dance organization — while the navy backgrounds provide a calm, professional, \n659:                 educational environment.\n660:                 </p>\n661:             </div>\n662:         </div>\n663:     </div>\n664: </div>\n665: \n666: <!-- 6. Technical Specification -->\n667: <div class=\"section\">\n668:     <h2 class=\"section-title\">06 &middot; Technical Specification</h2>\n669:     <div class=\"card\">\n670:         <table class=\"token-table\">\n671:             <tr><th>Property</th><th>Value</th><th>Notes</th></tr>\n672:             <tr><td>Format</td><td>PNG (RGB)</td><td>No alpha channel; background is pure black</td></tr>\n673:             <tr><td>Dimensions</td><td>974 &times; 992px</td><td>Near-square; 487:496 ratio</td></tr>\n674:             <tr><td>Resolution</td><td>216 DPI</td><td>Print-ready; ~4.5\" &times; 4.6\" physical</td></tr>\n675:             <tr><td>File Size</td><td>65,024 bytes</td><td>63.5 KB optimized PNG</td></tr>\n676:             <tr><td>Unique Colors</td><td>7,961</td><td>Includes anti-aliasing and gradient dithering</td></tr>\n677:             <tr><td>Primary Color</td><td>#000000 (92.1%)</td><td>Black background + text</td></tr>\n678:             <tr><td>Accent Gradient</td><td>#c08060 &rarr; #c04060</td><td>Copper-to-crimson, ~7.6% of pixels</td></tr>\n679:             <tr><td>Edge Density</td><td>0.91%</td><td>Clean, minimalist linework</td></tr>\n680:             <tr><td>Content BBox</td><td>(209, 238) 468 &times; 462</td><td>African continent outline</td></tr>\n681:             <tr><td>Text Regions</td><td>~28 connected components</td><td>\"AFJ\" (top) + \"CARDIFF\" (bottom)</td></tr>\n682:             <tr><td>Symmetry (H)</td><td>94.5%</td><td>Near-perfect horizontal mirror</td></tr>\n683:             <tr><td>Symmetry (V)</td><td>93.4%</td><td>Slight top-weight bias</td></tr>\n684:         </table>\n685:     </div>\n686: </div>\n687: \n688: <!-- 7. Comprehensive Glossary of All Terms -->\n689: <div class=\"section\">\n690:     <h2 class=\"section-title\">07 &middot; Glossary &mdash; Every Word Explained</h2>\n691:     <div class=\"card\">\n692:         <p style=\"color:var(--text-dim); margin-bottom:24px;\">\n693:         Every specialised term on this page is defined below with its rationale (why this word over alternatives),\n694:         its purpose (why the element or concept exists), what it enables or solves, and the scenarios it serves.\n695:         Terms are organised alphabetically. Use the letter bar to jump to a section.\n696:         </p>\n697: \n698:         <!-- Letter navigation -->\n699:         <div style=\"display:flex; gap:4px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-bottom:24px; padding-bottom:16px; border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);\">\n700:             <a href=\"#gloss-A\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">A</a>\n701:             <a href=\"#gloss-B\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">B</a>\n702:             <a href=\"#gloss-C\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">C</a>\n703:             <a href=\"#gloss-D\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">D</a>\n704:             <a href=\"#gloss-E\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">E</a>\n705:             <a href=\"#gloss-F\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">F</a>\n706:             <a href=\"#gloss-G\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">G</a>\n707:             <a href=\"#gloss-H\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">H</a>\n708:             <a href=\"#gloss-K\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">K</a>\n709:             <a href=\"#gloss-L\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">L</a>\n710:             <a href=\"#gloss-M\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">M</a>\n711:             <a href=\"#gloss-N\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">N</a>\n712:             <a href=\"#gloss-O\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">O</a>\n713:             <a href=\"#gloss-P\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">P</a>\n714:             <a href=\"#gloss-R\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">R</a>\n715:             <a href=\"#gloss-S\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">S</a>\n716:             <a href=\"#gloss-T\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">T</a>\n717:             <a href=\"#gloss-U\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">U</a>\n718:             <a href=\"#gloss-V\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">V</a>\n719:             <a href=\"#gloss-W\" style=\"color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.85rem; padding:2px 8px; border:1px solid var(--border); border-radius:4px;\">W</a>\n720:         </div>\n721: \n722:         <!-- GLOSSARY ENTRIES -->\n723: \n724:         <div id=\"gloss-A\" style=\"margin-bottom:32px;\">\n725:             <h3 style=\"font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:16px; color:var(--accent);\">A</h3>\n726: \n727:             <div style=\"background:var(--surface2); border-radius:8px; padding:16px; margin-bottom:16px; border-left:3px solid var(--accent);\">\n728:                 <div style=\"font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;\">accent gradient</div>\n729:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n730:                 <strong>Why \"accent\" not \"secondary\", \"highlight\", or \"pop colour\":</strong> In design-token systems, \"accent\" is the\n731:                 industry-standard term for the colour that provides visual emphasis against a dominant \"base\" or \"primary\". \n732:                 \"Secondary\" implies a supporting role for information, not emphasis. \"Highlight\" is reserved for UI selection states. \n733:                 \"Pop colour\" is colloquial and not machine-parseable in token pipelines. \"Accent\" is neutral, precise, and maps\n734:                 directly to CSS variables (<code>--accent</code>), design tool colour styles, and component props.\n735:                 </p>\n736:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n737:                 <strong>The gradient is copper-to-crimson (#c08060 → #c04060). Why a gradient, not a flat colour:</strong> A flat accent\n738:                 colour would make the continent read as a solid shape rather than a luminous, energetic form. The gradient simulates\n739:                 a light source moving diagonally (135°) across the surface, creating depth and a subtle \"glow\" that evokes fire, embers,\n740:                 and the warmth of the African continent. Flat colour would feel static and vector-like — appropriate for a tech logo\n741:                 but wrong for an Afro-dance organisation that wants to convey energy, movement, and passion.\n742:                 </p>\n743:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7;\">\n744:                 <strong>What it enables:</strong> (1) The gradient creates visual depth without requiring a separate shadow or highlight\n745:                 layer, keeping the file small. (2) It encodes brand emotion — copper = earth/heritage, crimson = energy/passion —\n746:                 in a single visual property. (3) It works across media: on screens the gradient animates subtly, in print it\n747:                 reproduces as a rich tonal range, on merchandise it can be replaced with foil stamping. (4) The specific angle\n748:                 (135°) and stops (20% copper → 50% amber → 100% crimson) are tuneable tokens that a developer can adjust in\n749:                 one place: <code>--accent-gradient: linear-gradient(135deg, #c08060 20%, #c0a040 50%, #c04060 100%)</code>.\n750:                 </p>\n751:             </div>\n752: \n753:             <div style=\"background:var(--surface2); border-radius:8px; padding:16px; margin-bottom:16px; border-left:3px solid var(--accent);\">\n754:                 <div style=\"font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;\">acronym (\"AFJ\")</div>\n755:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n756:                 <strong>Why \"acronym\" not \"initials\", \"abbreviation\", or \"logo mark\":</strong> \"AFJ\" stands for \"African and FunJive\" (the\n757:                 full registered name of the organisation). It is pronounced as three separate letters (/eɪ/ /ɛf/ /dʒeɪ/), making it\n758:                 an acronym rather than an initialism (where each letter sounds independently). In design, calling it an \"acronym\" \n759:                 signals that the letters represent expanded words, not standalone symbols. \"Logo mark\" would be confusing because\n760:                 the continent shape is the mark — the acronym is specifically the <em>textual identifier</em>.\n761:                 </p>\n762:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n763:                 <strong>Why it exists:</strong> The acronym is the single most recognisable identifier for AFJ Cardiff — dancers,\n764:                 students, and social-media followers all refer to the organisation as \"AFJ\" (never \"African and FunJive\"). It\n765:                 serves as the primary verbal hook and visual anchor.\n766:                 </p>\n767:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7;\">\n768:                 <strong>What it helps with:</strong> (1) Searchability — \"AFJ Cardiff\" is short enough for Instagram handles,\n769:                 hashtags, and URLs (afjcardiff.com). (2) Memorability — three letters are easier to recall than a full phrase,\n770:                 especially across languages. (3) Brand protection — the acronym can be trademarked as a word mark, providing\n771:                 legal coverage beyond the full name.\n772:                 </p>\n773:             </div>\n774: \n775:             <div style=\"background:var(--surface2); border-radius:8px; padding:16px; margin-bottom:16px; border-left:3px solid var(--accent);\">\n776:                 <div style=\"font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;\">African continent silhouette (primary element)</div>\n777:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n778:                 <strong>Why \"silhouette\" not \"outline\", \"shape\", \"map\", or \"icon\":</strong> \"Silhouette\" specifically means a filled\n779:                 shape with no internal detail — the continent is rendered as a solid form with a gradient fill, not a stroked\n780:                 outline. An \"outline\" would use a thin stroke and transparent fill, which would look weak against the black\n781:                 background. \"Map\" implies geographic accuracy with borders and labels, which this is not — it is an abstracted,\n782:                 stylised form. \"Icon\" is too generic. \"Silhouette\" captures the solid, monolithic quality of the visual.\n783:                 </p>\n784:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n785:                 <strong>Why a continent silhouette at all:</strong> The silhouette grounds the brand in African heritage without\n786:                 requiring words. It functions as a <em>pictorial mark</em> — a symbol that communicates origin instantly, even\n787:                 when the text is too small to read (e.g. favicon, social-media avatar, merchandise tag). It also establishes\n788:                 the brand's cultural authenticity: AFJ Cardiff is not a generic dance studio, it is specifically an <em>Afro</em>\n789:                 dance organisation.\n790:                 </p>\n791:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7;\">\n792:                 <strong>Why \"primary element\" not \"main graphic\" or \"central image\":</strong> In design-system nomenclature, a\n793:                 \"primary element\" is the single most important visual component — everything else (typography, margins, secondary\n794:                 shapes) supports or defers to it. Saying \"main graphic\" is ambiguous (main how? size? colour? importance?).\n795:                 \"Primary element\" is the formal design-token term used in systems like Material Design, Lightning Design System,\n796:                 and Spectrum. It helps developers and designers make consistent prioritisation decisions: the continent gets\n797:                 the strongest gradient, the most central position, and the most generous surrounding space.\n798:                 </p>\n799:             </div>\n800: \n801:             <div style=\"background:var(--surface2); border-radius:8px; padding:16px; margin-bottom:16px; border-left:3px solid var(--accent);\">\n802:                 <div style=\"font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;\">amber / gold (#c0a040)</div>\n803:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n804:                 <strong>Why \"amber\" not \"yellow\", \"golden\", \"honey\", or \"mustard\":</strong> The hex #c0a040 sits at RGB(192,160,64) —\n805:                 a desaturated, warm yellow with significant red bias. \"Yellow\" (#ffff00) is too pure, too neon, and reads as\n806:                 a primary colour rather than a brand accent. \"Golden\" is subjective (any yellow-brown could be called golden).\n807:                 \"Honey\" is a food reference that doesn't belong in a brand palette. \"Mustard\" reads as unpleasantly green-tinged.\n808:                 \"Amber\" is the most precise everyday word: amber (the fossilised resin) has exactly this warm, translucent\n809:                 golden-brown hue. More importantly, \"amber\" is the standard term for this hue in design systems (Material Design\n810:                 uses \"amber\" for #ffc107-range colours) and in colour science (the CIE colour system identifies amber as a\n811:                 distinct region around 575–585 nm). Paired with \"gold\", it clarifies that the colour sits at the warm,\n812:                 slightly brown end of the gold spectrum — not a metallic gold (#d4af37) but a matte, earthy amber-gold.\n813:                 </p>\n814:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n815:                 <strong>Why this colour exists at 12.4% of accent:</strong> Amber provides the mid-tone transition in the warm\n816:                 gradient — it bridges the copper (darker, red-brown) and the pale gold/lighter accents. Without amber, the\n817:                 gradient would jump from copper directly to bright white, losing the nuanced warm-to-hot transition that makes\n818:                 the continent feel lit from within.\n819:                 </p>\n820:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7;\">\n821:                 <strong>Scenarios:</strong> (1) On dark backgrounds, amber creates a \"lit ember\" effect that draws the eye.\n822:                 (2) As a text colour on black, it meets WCAG AA contrast at large sizes (ratio ~5.5:1) while being warmer\n823:                 than pure white. (3) In gradients with crimson, amber shifts the mood from \"fire\" to \"sunset\" — useful for\n824:                 hero sections vs. detail cards. (4) As a hover state accent, amber feels inviting without the alarm of crimson.\n825:                 </p>\n826:             </div>\n827: \n828:             <div style=\"background:var(--surface2); border-radius:8px; padding:16px; margin-bottom:16px; border-left:3px solid var(--accent);\">\n829:                 <div style=\"font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;\">anti-aliasing</div>\n830:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n831:                 <strong>Why \"anti-aliasing\" not \"smoothing\", \"blending\", or \"sub-pixel rendering\":</strong> \"Anti-aliasing\" is the\n832:                 correct technical term for the algorithm that softens jagged edges (aliasing) by inserting semi-transparent\n833:                 or blended-colour pixels at shape boundaries. \"Smoothing\" is ambiguous (could mean Gaussian blur, median filter,\n834:                 or bézier curve optimisation). \"Blending\" covers many unrelated effects (layer blend modes, gradient mixing).\n835:                 \"Sub-pixel rendering\" is a specific LCD technique (ClearType) that's different from classic anti-aliasing.\n836:                 </p>\n837:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n838:                 <strong>Why it matters for the colour count (7,961 unique):</strong> Anti-aliasing pixels are the reason the\n839:                 logo has 7,961 unique colours instead of ~6 (the gradient + black + white). Each edge pixel along the continent\n840:                 outline and letterforms is a blend between the warm gradient and the black background, generating thousands of\n841:                 intermediate RGB values. This is expected — a logo with fewer than 100 unique colours would mean zero\n842:                 anti-aliasing, which would look pixelated and unprofessional on high-DPI screens.\n843:                 </p>\n844:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7;\">\n845:                 <strong>What it helps with / scenarios:</strong> (1) On Retina/HiDPI screens, anti-aliased edges appear smooth\n846:                 at any size — critical for logo display on modern phones and laptops. (2) In print (216 DPI), anti-aliasing\n847:                 ensures the continent edge doesn't look jagged when printed at 4.5 inches wide. (3) When the logo is used as a\n848:                 favicon (16–32px), anti-aliasing is the only thing preventing the continent from becoming an unidentifiable blob.\n849:                 (4) For developers: if you convert this PNG to SVG, the anti-aliased edges tell you exactly where the original\n850:                 path boundaries lie, making tracing more accurate.\n851:                 </p>\n852:             </div>\n853:         </div>\n854: \n855:         <div id=\"gloss-B\" style=\"margin-bottom:32px;\">\n856:             <h3 style=\"font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:16px; color:var(--accent);\">B</h3>\n857: \n858:             <div style=\"background:var(--surface2); border-radius:8px; padding:16px; margin-bottom:16px; border-left:3px solid var(--accent);\">\n859:                 <div style=\"font-family:var(--mono); font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600; margin-bottom:4px;\">black base (#000000)</div>\n860:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n861:                 <strong>Why \"black base\" not \"background black\" or \"dark mode\":</strong> \"Base\" is the design-token term for the\n862:                 foundational colour everything sits on. \"Background\" implies it's just behind content — but this colour also\n863:                 appears in the typography and other elements (it's the text colour for any inverted version). \"Base\" signals\n864:                 that it serves multiple roles: background, text colour, and the starting point for all colour calculations.\n865:                 \"Dark mode\" is a runtime preference; this logo uses a black base regardless of system theme — it's the brand\n866:                 colour, not a theme choice.\n867:                 </p>\n868:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7; margin-bottom:8px;\">\n869:                 <strong>Why 92.1% black, not 100% or 50%:</strong> At the pixel level, 92.1% of the canvas is pure #000000.\n870:                 The remaining 7.9% is gradient pixels (the continent, text, and anti-aliasing). 100% black would mean no logo\n871:                 at all — just a black rectangle. The dominant black coverage is intentional: it creates a dramatic,\n872:                 high-contrast stage where the warm gradient appears to float in darkness, like a fire in a dark room.\n873:                 </p>\n874:                 <p style=\"font-size:0.85rem; color:var(--text-dim); line-height:1.7;\">\n875:                 <strong>What it enables:</strong> (1) The black base acts as a \"silent background\" that makes the small area of\n876:                 accent colour (7.6%) feel disproportionately impactful — a technique called \"colour economy\". (2) It drastically\n877:                 reduces the image file size because large uniform black areas compress extremely well in PNG (each repeated\n878:                 pixel is encoded as a short run-length). (3) It provides a natural canvas for the Classroom UI palette (navy\n879:                 #202040, charcoal #202020) — the logo's black background would blend into those dark UI surfaces, which is why\n880:                 the accent gradient needs to be bright enough to pop. (4) For merchandise (t-shirts, hoodies), a mostly-black\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-880. Use offset=881 to continue.)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
